    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Wuhan Union Hospital, China</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study aims to verify the efficacy and safety of Qizhiweitong granule on Chinese patients
      with functional dyspepsia diagnosed by the Rome III criteria. It includes two subtypes of
      functional dyspepsia, postprandial distress syndrome or abdominal pain syndrome.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
